line_1: To keep the matrimonial bond unstain'd;
line_2: With close fidelity and love unfeign'd,

line_1: "By pain untroubled, and by sin unstain'd;
My Heart's unconquer'd, and my Soul unstain'd,
line_2: A Fortitude by Heav'n it self maintain'd;

line_1: Unwarp'd by folly, and by vice unstain'd,
line_2: The prize of virtue has, for ever gain'd!

line_1: Skimm'd lightly o'er the tide, undipt, unstain'd,
line_2: Though with the crowd to pass the flood constrain'd,

line_1: Skimm'd lightly o'er the tide, undipt, unstain'd,
line_2: By hireling guides and in all depths sustain'd,

line_1: Skimm'd lightly o'er the tide, undipt, unstain'd,
line_2: And aye their proud prerogative maintain'd,
